# Cloudinary Configuration - SECURE TEMPLATE
# Copy this file to .env and replace with your actual values

# ✅ SAFE - These can be public (used with EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix):
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud-name-here
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=learn_local_uploads
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_AVATAR_UPLOAD_PRESET=learn_local_avatars

# ❌ NEVER ADD THESE TO CLIENT-SIDE .env:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=xxx
# EXPO_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=xxx
#
# ⚠️ The EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix exposes values in your app bundle!
# API credentials should ONLY be used server-side.
# For mobile apps, use unsigned upload presets (configured above).

# =============================================================================
# HOW TO USE:
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    Windows: copy env.template .env
#    Mac/Linux: cp env.template .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and replace 'your-cloud-name-here' with your actual cloud name
#    (Get from: https://console.cloudinary.com/)
#
# 3. Make sure upload preset 'learn_local_uploads' exists in Cloudinary:
#    - Settings → Upload → Upload presets
#    - Signing Mode: Unsigned
#
# 4. Restart app: npx expo start --clear
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES:
# =============================================================================
# ✅ Only cloud name and upload preset are needed for client-side uploads
# ✅ .env is in .gitignore (never committed to git)
# ✅ API secrets belong on backend/server only
# ❌ Never use EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix for secrets/keys
# ❌ Never commit .env to version control
# ❌ Never hardcode credentials in code or docs
#
# For more info, see: Guides/CLOUDINARY_SETUP.md

